reviews.review_text: Thanks for the upload Nice to see gems like this popup unexpectedly. And the sound is very good for the time period. A Sony cassette recorder fed by some AKG mics in a good location, recording on the best tapes available at the time. These were a definite labor of love. I record to digital now, having started out with DAT. Hats off to those who prior to digital. I know it wasn't easy with all the stuff you had to lug about. Thanks again! Very much appreciated.
